7: // The Lambda (logistic) map is the complex analogue of the real logistic equation.
8: // It is conformally conjugate to z² + c near the fixed points, making its Julia
9: // sets topologically similar to quadratic Julia sets but with a different parameter
10: // space geometry. With λ = (1.0, 0.30) the critical point z = 1/2 lies in the
11: // bounded component, producing a connected Julia set with a compact central body
12: // and intricate boundary filaments tracing the bifurcation structure of the
13: // complex logistic family.
14: // Derivative: λ·(1−2z)·der — Julia mode (no +1 term).
15: // Supports normal-map shading (colorScheme 50-63).
